{
  "text": "In 2002 we reported a cohort of 107 differentiated thyroid carcinoma patients thought to be free of disease and studied them with recombinant human TSH (rhTSH; Genzyme Corp., Cambridge, MA.) mediated diagnostic whole-body scan (DxWBS) and stim-Tg (rhTSH-Tg) [CITATION_1] . Patients were stratified into three groups according to their rhTSH-Tg responses: group 1, Tg less than 0.5 ng/ml (68 patients); group 2, Tg from 0.6 to 2.0 ng/ml (19 patients); and group 3, Tg greater than 2 ng/ml (20 patients).",
  "correct_citation": {
